text:
Hi guys, If you don’t know this already, we have a change of plans for our next iteration. 

We will be building the Android app for our own project, not someone else’s. Tomorrow we will be handed an Android device - one per group. 

What I wanted to ask each one of you is who will be responsible for that device. I suggest it to be a person who does not have an Android device already. 

Question: Who hasn’t got an Android phone/tablet already? 

I can probably get one, so I will take it only if everyone else has one
Does anyone here have android dev experience?
I'm familiar with a bit of the tooling, but I haven't actually written any Android code.
We have an intern at Honda who is a pro. I can't ask him to write code for us - that would be cheating - but I can ask him questions if we are really stuck
Personally, I have only written C++ code on Android for some highly specific shader code as part of my research.
I do. I wrote my software engineering 1 android app a year ago in Java
I'm slightly familiar I touched it about three years ago so it's been a while haha
Also, I just want to let you guys know that I am going to be away from the 3rd to 7th without a comp. I will try my best to keep updated on slack and make up for the lost time when I get back!
